 Math: The Math namespace object contains static properties and methods for mathematical constants and functions.
 Math works with the Number type. It doesn't work with BigInt.

 1: Constants:
  Math.PI: Represents the mathematical constant Pi (Ï€).
 const piValue = Math.PI;
 console.log(piValue);

 2. Basic Operations:

 1  Math.abs(): The Math.abs() static method returns the absolute value of a number.
 or in simple, how far the number is from 0. It will be always positive

 2  Math.round(x): Rounds a number to the nearest integer.

 3 Math.ceil(x): Returns the value of x rounded up to its nearest integer:

 4 Math.floor(x): Returns the value of x rounded down to its nearest integer.

 5 Math.trunc(x): Returns the integer part of x:

code:----------------------------------------------------------------------------
// 1  Math.PI 
const pivalue = Math.PI;
console.log(pivalue);
//2  Math.abs()
console.log(Math.abs(25)); // output 25
